The VirtualSpeechChoice (13) type is used to apply settings to SpeechContext lines.

The type is used to determine under what circumstances the line can be triggered and
how frequently it can be used. Unlike SpeechChoice, VirtualSpeechChoice does not require a speaker,
and is instead triggered as a response to a speaker's line. It is mostly used on generic street ped
conversation lines.


Fields:

Field name  Type      FileRef Description
--
Name        metahash  dat151  VirtualSpeechChoice name from Dat151SpeechContext <Unk09>.
Flags       flags             Unknown flags
Unk01       metahash          Unknown
Unk02       metahash          Unknown //unused
Unk03       integer           Unknown
Unk04       metahash          Unknown //unused      
Unk05       metahash          Unknown //unused
Unk06       metahash          Unknown //unused
Unk07       byte              Unknown
Unk08       byte              Unknown
Unk09       byte              Unknown
Items       item list         Item list of Dat151SpeechChoice.




Examples:

<Item type="VirtualSpeechChoice" ntOffset="361220">
 <Name>generic_curse_virtual_sc</Name>
 <Flags value="0xAAA94000" />
 <Unk01>hash_05C6BAAF</Unk01>
 <Unk02 />
 <Unk03 value="-1" />
 <Unk04 />
 <Unk05 />
 <Unk06 />
 <Unk07 value="3" />
 <Unk08 value="0" />
 <Unk09 value="2" />
 <Items>
  <Item>generic_curse_high_sc</Item>
  <Item>generic_curse_med_sc</Item>
 </Items>
</Item>